    comment: '<p><em><code>localStorage</code></em> is a storage object used to store data in without an expiry date. A local storage object can be accessed to add (store), access, and remove data. Data stored in <em><code>localStorage</code></em> will remain there once the current browsing session ends and the browser has been closed.</p>\n<p>To create an item in local storage, pass in the item key and the item value:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-javascript">localStorage.setItem(\'country\', \'England\');\n</code></pre>\n<p>Retrieving data from local storage:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-javascript">var localData =   \n    localStorage.getItem("country");\nconsole.log(localData); // prints \'England\'\n</code></pre>\n<p>Removing an item and clearing all data from local storage:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-javascript">localStorage.removeItem(\'country\');\nlocalStorage.clear();\n</code></pre>\n<p>If more websites try to store data with the same key, the old values will be overwritten.</p>\n',
